response: "{ \"title\": \"Longest Increasing Subsequence\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, find the length of the longest increasing subsequence. A subsequence is a sequence that can be derived from another sequence by deleting some elements without changing the order of the remaining elements.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef longest_increasing_subsequence(nums: list[int)) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the length of the longest increasing subsequence in the input list.\", \"code\": \"def longest_increasing_subsequence(nums: list[int)) -> int:\\n    n = len(nums)\\n    dp = [1] * n\\n    for i in range(1, n):\\n        for j in range(i):\\n            if nums[i] > nums[j]:\\n                dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1)\\n    return max(dp)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([10, 9, 2, 5, 3, 7, 101, 18]) == 4\", \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 6\", \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([-1, -2, -3, -4, -5]) == 1\", \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([7, 7, 7, 7, 7]) == 1\"] }"
